<LP>
   PHILADELPHIA -- Bell Atlantic Corp. said it completed the
purchase of the mid-Atlantic regional PBX operations of
Northern Telecom Ltd.'s Meridian Business Systems Group.
Terms weren't disclosed.
   As part of the transaction, the company's Bell Atlanticom
Systems, Inc. unit acquired a base of 500,000 private branch
exchange ports serving 1,800 customers. The unit also became
an authorized U.S. distributor of Meridian's SL-1 and SL-100
PBX systems.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   In addition, about 560 Northern Telecom workers became
employees of the Bell Atlantic unit. Northern Telecom is a
unit of BCE Inc. of Canada.
</TEXT>
